WEBVTT

00:06.264 --> 00:07.731
(siren blaring)

00:07.733 --> 00:08.933
(crowd chatter)

00:08.935 --> 00:10.868
First on the scene?
Yup.

00:10.870 --> 00:11.699
What we got?

00:11.700 --> 00:13.398
Victim's coming out
of the synagogue here.

00:13.400 --> 00:15.567
Some guy on a motorcycle
rode on the sidewalk,

00:15.568 --> 00:17.102
shot him in the head
and rode off.

00:17.104 --> 00:19.037
CSU and MLI
just arrived.

00:19.039 --> 00:21.807
Witnesses?
One. The man sitting on the steps.

00:21.809 --> 00:23.075
He's the rabbi.

00:23.077 --> 00:24.409
Son of a gun.

00:24.411 --> 00:26.011
(garbled radio transmission)

00:26.013 --> 00:28.180
Cover him up, okay?
Sure thing.

00:28.182 --> 00:29.648
I think I recognize this guy.

00:29.650 --> 00:31.249
(siren blaring)

00:31.251 --> 00:33.618
Rabbi?
Yes.

00:33.620 --> 00:35.087
Detective Reagan and Baez.

00:35.089 --> 00:37.656
You mind if we ask you
a few questions?

00:37.658 --> 00:39.858
Sorry. You know...

00:41.294 --> 00:43.829
He was my good friend.

00:43.831 --> 00:45.430
Herman Kleiner?

00:45.432 --> 00:46.932
Judge Herman
Kleiner, you know?

00:46.934 --> 00:49.334
Judge Kleiner from the Bronx, yeah.
That's right.

00:49.336 --> 00:51.369
We had our weekly meeting.

00:51.371 --> 00:54.439
He's, uh, a member of
the executive committee.

00:54.441 --> 00:57.542
We'd come out for
our, uh, walk.

00:57.544 --> 00:59.611
Traditionally, we take
a small cigar together

00:59.613 --> 01:01.313
after the meeting.

01:01.315 --> 01:03.214
You happen to get a look
at the shooter?

01:03.216 --> 01:07.252
No. All happened so fast,
and he was wearing a helmet

01:07.254 --> 01:11.222
with a... you know,
a mask, a-a-a...

01:11.224 --> 01:12.157
A visor?

01:12.159 --> 01:13.691
BAEZ:
What makes you say

01:13.693 --> 01:14.693
it was a he?

01:14.694 --> 01:15.694
He spoke.

01:15.695 --> 01:17.362
What did he say?

01:17.364 --> 01:20.465
He-he was idling by the curb

01:20.467 --> 01:24.235
and he called out
“Herman Irving Kleiner.”

01:24.237 --> 01:28.406
And, uh, we looked over,
and he came at us.

01:28.408 --> 01:29.774
That's all he said?

01:29.776 --> 01:32.010
He just yelled out
the judge's name, nothing else?

01:32.012 --> 01:34.345
His full name, almost
the way that, uh,

01:34.347 --> 01:38.683
the parent addresses
the unruly child.

01:38.685 --> 01:40.384
(phone ringing)
Excuse me.

01:40.386 --> 01:42.153
I'm sorry.

01:42.155 --> 01:43.521
This is my wife.

01:43.523 --> 01:46.023
That's all right.
Take it outside the tape, okay?

01:47.826 --> 01:50.895
What do you think?

01:50.897 --> 01:53.364
Judge Kleiner's got
a longstanding reputation

01:53.366 --> 01:56.100
as the toughest hanging judge
in all of the Bronx.

01:56.102 --> 01:58.236
“Long Term Her”"
they call him.

01:58.238 --> 01:59.403
So you're thinking

01:59.405 --> 02:01.405
someone got out of prison
looking for revenge?

02:01.407 --> 02:03.874
I think if somebody wanted
their revenge on the judge,

02:03.876 --> 02:05.276
they got it.

02:05.278 --> 02:07.211
Let's get to work.

02:09.881 --> 02:13.451
What, if anything, did you find
inside the canister?

02:13.453 --> 02:14.752
I recovered
a .38 caliber revolver

02:14.754 --> 02:15.920
from inside the canister.

02:15.922 --> 02:17.121
Can you tell us

02:17.123 --> 02:19.123
the ballistics report
on that gun?

02:19.125 --> 02:20.724
They match the bullets found

02:20.726 --> 02:23.394
in the skull of the victim,
Thomas Dunne.

02:23.396 --> 02:25.129
ERIN: And what did you do
with that gun?

02:25.131 --> 02:27.398
I vouchered it with the property clerk.
Can you

02:27.400 --> 02:28.966
walk us through
the vouchering process?

02:28.968 --> 02:30.201
Uh, procedure is,

02:30.203 --> 02:32.937
I safeguard the weapon,
bring it back to my command,

02:32.939 --> 02:35.339
obtain a voucher,
and using a scribe,

02:35.341 --> 02:37.775
scratch my initials
on the frame.

02:38.743 --> 02:41.412
Detective,

02:41.414 --> 02:44.281
is this the gun that you found

02:44.283 --> 02:46.150
inside the sugar canister

02:46.152 --> 02:49.420
in Mr. Martin's apartment?

02:56.761 --> 02:59.663
No, I don't believe it is.

02:59.665 --> 03:01.999
Are you sure?

03:03.368 --> 03:05.068
Yes, ma'am.

03:05.070 --> 03:06.503
I don't see my initials.

03:06.505 --> 03:08.739
This is not the gun I vouchered.

03:08.741 --> 03:10.974
(gallery murmuring)

03:18.449 --> 03:19.950
(sighs)

03:19.952 --> 03:21.852
(knocking)
Sir?

03:21.854 --> 03:23.653
Punch me out, Baker.
You, too.

03:23.655 --> 03:27.224
DCPI Moore and Special Assistant
Gormley asked me to keep you.

03:27.226 --> 03:28.892
For?

03:28.894 --> 03:30.760
They're on their way up
from the second floor.

03:30.762 --> 03:32.696
Sorry to keep you.

03:32.698 --> 03:35.532
Am I gonna be sorry you did?

03:35.534 --> 03:36.933
Uh, Sid?

03:36.935 --> 03:38.101
Sergeant.

03:38.103 --> 03:39.669
About a half hour ago,

03:39.671 --> 03:41.204
one Joshua Greenwald,

03:41.206 --> 03:43.473
a prominent Manhattan attorney,
was shot

03:43.475 --> 03:45.909
by an assailant
riding a motorcycle

03:45.911 --> 03:47.911
outside a restaurant
on the Lower East Side.

03:47.913 --> 03:50.947
He was DOA at the scene.

03:50.949 --> 03:52.215
Witnesses?

03:52.217 --> 03:54.250
Three of his colleagues
from the office.

03:54.252 --> 03:56.286
And they also heard
the assailant

03:56.288 --> 03:58.988
call out the victim
by his full name?

03:58.990 --> 04:01.524
Two nights, two hits,
both victims Jewish.

04:01.526 --> 04:04.627
Both shot by a guy
on a motorcycle.

04:04.629 --> 04:08.831
Baker, call Shanghai Luck
and order us all some dinner.

04:14.972 --> 04:17.140
Okay, watch your step.

04:17.142 --> 04:18.841
We're back here
again Sunday night

04:18.843 --> 04:20.709
from, from 6:00 to 9:00,

04:20.712 --> 04:22.512
so, uh, check back with me.

04:22.514 --> 04:24.147
Thank you so much.

04:24.149 --> 04:25.515
<i>De nada.</i>

04:25.517 --> 04:26.649
You feel better.

04:26.651 --> 04:29.352
Thank you.

04:29.354 --> 04:31.621
Hello?

04:31.623 --> 04:33.723
We're open for ten more minutes
if you want to...

04:33.725 --> 04:35.591
<i>Estamos</i>

04:35.593 --> 04:37.527
<i>abiertos Durante diez</i>

04:37.529 --> 04:38.995
<i>minutos mas...</i>

04:38.997 --> 04:41.063
(screams) Keep your mouth shut
and give me your money!

04:41.065 --> 04:42.065
Give me the money now!

04:42.066 --> 04:43.099
Oh, God. You know what?

04:43.101 --> 04:44.634
Give me your money now!
I have $20!

04:44.636 --> 04:47.169
That's all I got! Just take it,
I swear, please, please...

04:47.171 --> 04:48.004
Okay.

04:48.006 --> 04:51.207
(grunting)
Okay.

04:51.209 --> 04:53.109
The wedding ring!
Take off your wedding ring!

04:53.111 --> 04:55.644
Give me the wedding ring now!

04:57.014 --> 04:58.848
No!

04:58.850 --> 05:01.917
No! No!

05:03.086 --> 05:04.520
No! No!

05:04.522 --> 05:06.322
MAN: Nurse?
Call 911!

05:06.324 --> 05:09.525
Are you okay?
(mumbling)

